Final' is used when this transaction is not the first transaction within a cycle but is the last. An "F" transaction may contain "Output" which its receiver will use to update files, electronic or paper.
Initial' is used to indicate that this is the first transaction within a Transaction Processing Cycle and that response indicates further transactions within this cycle are anticipated.

?Intermediate? is used when this transaction is not the first transaction within a Transaction Processing Cycle and is not expected to be the last. During the Input Phase of a Transaction Processing Cycle, the "M" code can be used only for Simple Acknowledgements and Interim Memos or Print transactions. ?Output?  is used when this transaction is not the first  transaction within a cycle and is not expected to be the last.  Unlike the Intermediate (M) Transaction, Output Transactions contain data (in any Automation Level). These are the result of transaction processing by the receiver of the Initial Transaction, and are sent in order to update the sender's (of the Initial Transaction) files, electronic or paper.
